# Cursor Rules for Palestinian Student Fund Project

## Project Context
- Next.js project with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS
- Bilingual support (Arabic/English) with language switching
- Multiple media-heavy pages with images and videos
- Deployed on Vercel Pro

## Media Optimization TODO (Future Task)
- Images and videos are loading slowly despite Next.js optimization and Vercel Pro
- Current issues: mixed usage of `<img>` and `<Image>` tags, large file sizes
- Solutions to implement later:
  1. Replace all `<img>` tags with Next.js `<Image>` components
  2. Add proper `sizes`, `priority`, and `loading` attributes
  3. Implement lazy loading for below-fold content
  4. Consider Image CDN services (Cloudinary/ImageKit/Cloudflare) for high-traffic scenarios
  5. Compress existing media files before upload

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow Next.js 13+ App Router patterns
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper accessibility (alt tags, ARIA labels)
- Support RTL languages (Arabic) with proper direction handling

## Component Patterns
- Use client components when needed for interactivity
- Implement proper error boundaries and loading states
- Follow the existing component structure in `/components` directory
- Use the UI components from `/components/ui` for consistency

## Performance Considerations
- Implement proper image optimization
- Use Next.js built-in performance features
- Consider lazy loading for non-critical content
- Optimize bundle size and implement code splitting

## Translation System
- Use the existing language provider system
- Support both Arabic and English content
- Handle RTL layout properly
- Use translation keys consistently

## File Organization
- Keep components in `/components` directory
- Use `/lib` for utility functions
- Store media files in `/public` with organized subdirectories
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions for pages
